And this is much clearer in the case of man, first, from the affection which exists between children and parents, which cannot be destroyed, except by detestable wickedness, secondly, in that a like feeling of love has arisen, if we discovered some actual person with whose character and nature we synipathize, because in him we seem to see, as it were, a shining light of integrity and virtue.
